name: Advent-of-Code
description: A repository for my implementations of the annual "Advent of Code" challenges. First attempted year was 2020. For more information see https://adventofcode.com/about.

name: edgorman.github.io
description: My personal website hosted on Github pages. It emulates a CLI by using the JQuery Terminal library, and allows file traversal of all my public repositories via submodules.

name: One-More-Neuron
description: Exploring the usage of reinforcement learning algorithms in my recreation of the game 'One More Brick' (similar to Brick Breaker) to create an AI that can automatically play the game.

name: phgorman.com
description: A personal website for my sibling (Peter Gorman). Used to demonstrate his out of work projects and post about thoughts and ideas he has.

name: Plex-Photo-Extractor
description: A chrome extension for downloading content from a plex server. Not available on the Chrome Webstore.

name: Property-Fundamentals
description: Investigating the automated collection and analysis of housing data from any location within the UK.

name: Quadris
description: Quadris is a Tetris-like game written in Godot and (soon to be re-) deployed on the Google Play Store. Available without purchase and without ads. Definitely not Tetris.

name: URL-Analyser
description: A malicious URL detection system using Machine Learning. This was presented as the dissertation for my BSc Computer Science degree at University of Southampton, which received a First-Class honours mark.

name: Voxel-Engine
description: A 3D rendering engine built in Java without any dependencies.  Implements a rasterization approach. Also contains voxel terrain generation, so it's basically becoming a Minecraft clone.
